# Remote Agents

AI agents that run automatically in response to Azure DevOps events. No developer action needed beyond adding a tag or creating a PR.

## How It Works

1. You add a **tag** to a work item in ADO (or create a PR)
2. ADO fires a webhook to AWS Lambda
3. Lambda checks for duplicates and rate limits, then queues an ADO Pipeline
4. The pipeline runs the AI agent
5. The agent posts results as **ADO comments** on the work item or PR

## Work Item Agents

All work-item agents require **two tags**: the agent-specific tag AND `KAI-TRIGGER`. Add the agent tag first, then `KAI-TRIGGER` when ready.

| Agent | Tag | Works on | Result |
|-------|-----|----------|--------|
| DoR Check | `KAI-DOR-AUTOMATION` | User Story | Readiness checklist — what's clear, what's missing |
| DoD Check | `KAI-DOD-AUTOMATION` | User Story | Pass/fail completion checklist |
| Estimation | `KAI-ESTIMATION-AUTOMATION` | User Story | Story points with reasoning |
| Bug Fix | `KAI-BUGFIX-AUTOMATION` | Bug | Triage analysis; may create branch + PR |
| Dev Agent | `KAI-DEV-AUTOMATION` | User Story | Branch + PR with implementation |
| QA Agent | `KAI-QA-AUTOMATION` | User Story | Screenshots and verification findings |
| Doc Agent | `KAI-DOC-AUTOMATION` | User Story | Wiki page with authoring guide |

## Pull Request Agents

These trigger automatically — no tags needed.

| Agent | Trigger | Result |
|-------|---------|--------|
| PR Review | PR created targeting base branch | Review comments with severity levels |
| PR Answer | Someone comments on your PR | Reply in the PR thread |

## Tracking Progress

- **Pipeline runs** — ADO > Pipelines > select the agent pipeline > recent runs
- **Work item comments** — the agent posts directly on the ticket
- **PR comments** — PR agents post directly on the pull request

## Troubleshooting

| Problem | Check |
|---------|-------|
| Tag added but nothing happened | `KAI-TRIGGER` tag also present? |
| Agent ran but no comment | Pipeline run logs for errors |
| PR Review didn't run | PR must target the base branch (usually `development`) |
| Was working, now stopped | ADO disables webhooks after 7 consecutive failures — re-enable in Service Hooks settings |
| Webhook delivered but no pipeline | Lambda logs in CloudWatch |

For detailed ops troubleshooting, see [runbook.md](runbook.md). For project-specific pipeline links and webhook details, see [automation/docs/how-to-trigger.md](../automation/docs/how-to-trigger.md).

## Safety Controls

| Control | What it does |
|---------|-------------|
| Rate limits | Per-pipeline daily cap (e.g., 50 PR reviews/day) |
| Token budget | Monthly spending cap; alerts at 80%, halts at 100% |
| Deduplication | Duplicate webhook events silently dropped (1h TTL) |
| Policy gates | Agents can only do what their role allows |
| Push policy | Code changes need 4 checks before pushing |
| Scanner | Prompt injection detection on all inputs |
